---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Water Quality Monitoring Methods and Analysis — jtdub.com"
  description="Comprehensive water quality monitoring protocols and environmental anthropology analysis for community science initiatives."
  zone="field"
>
  <section class="tst-page" data-zone="field">
    <header class="tst-page__header">
      <nav class="tst-page__breadcrumb" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
        <a href="/field">Field</a>
        <span aria-hidden="true">›</span>
        <a href="/community-science">Community Science</a>
        <span aria-hidden="true">›</span>
        <span>Water Quality Monitoring</span>
      </nav>
      <h1 class="tst-page__title">Water Quality Monitoring Methods and Analysis</h1>
      <p class="tst-page__lede">
        Community-based water quality monitoring program demonstrating
        standardized protocols and their relevance to environmental anthropology
        and sustainability research.
      </p>
    </header>

    <div class="tst-page__section">
      <h2>Standardized Monitoring Protocols</h2>
      <p>
        Water quality monitoring employs standardized methods to ensure data
        consistency and comparability across temporal and spatial scales. These
        protocols are essential for community science initiatives and
        professional environmental monitoring.
      </p>

      <div class="tst-page__protocol-grid">
        <div class="tst-page__protocol">
          <h3>Dissolved Oxygen (DO)</h3>
          <dl>
            <dt>Method</dt><dd>Electronic probe measurement (mg/L)</dd>
            <dt>Protocol</dt><dd>Calibrate probe daily, measure at multiple depths, record temperature simultaneously</dd>
            <dt>Significance</dt><dd>Critical indicator of aquatic ecosystem health. Values below 5 mg/L stress aquatic life; below 2 mg/L cause fish kills</dd>
            <dt>Factors</dt><dd>Temperature-dependent, affected by organic pollution, algal blooms, and thermal stratification</dd>
          </dl>
        </div>

        <div class="tst-page__protocol">
          <h3>pH Levels</h3>
          <dl>
            <dt>Method</dt><dd>Calibrated electronic pH meter (standard units)</dd>
            <dt>Protocol</dt><dd>Two-point calibration (pH 7.0, 10.0), temperature compensation, multiple readings</dd>
            <dt>Significance</dt><dd>Indicates acid-base balance. Natural waters: 6.5–8.5; values outside this range stress aquatic organisms</dd>
            <dt>Factors</dt><dd>Influenced by geology, acid rain, agricultural runoff, and biological processes</dd>
          </dl>
        </div>

        <div class="tst-page__protocol">
          <h3>Turbidity</h3>
          <dl>
            <dt>Method</dt><dd>Nephelometric measurement (NTU)</dd>
            <dt>Protocol</dt><dd>Use turbidity meter, collect sample avoiding air bubbles, measure within 24 hours</dd>
            <dt>Significance</dt><dd>Measures suspended particles. High turbidity reduces light penetration, affects photosynthesis and aquatic habitats</dd>
            <dt>Factors</dt><dd>Erosion, construction, agricultural practices, urban runoff, and natural events</dd>
          </dl>
        </div>

        <div class="tst-page__protocol">
          <h3>Conductivity</h3>
          <dl>
            <dt>Method</dt><dd>Electronic conductivity meter (µS/cm)</dd>
            <dt>Protocol</dt><dd>Temperature-compensated readings, calibration with standard solutions, multiple measurements</dd>
            <dt>Significance</dt><dd>Indicates dissolved ion concentrations. Useful for detecting pollution and salinity changes</dd>
            <dt>Factors</dt><dd>Geology, road salt, sewage discharge, industrial pollution, and natural mineral content</dd>
          </dl>
        </div>

        <div class="tst-page__protocol">
          <h3>Water Clarity</h3>
          <dl>
            <dt>Method</dt><dd>Secchi disk measurement (centimeters or meters)</dd>
            <dt>Protocol</dt><dd>Lower black and white disk until no longer visible, record depth, repeat measurement</dd>
            <dt>Significance</dt><dd>Simple but effective measure of water transparency, related to turbidity and productivity</dd>
            <dt>Factors</dt><dd>Suspended sediments, algal growth, organic matter, and seasonal variations</dd>
          </dl>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="tst-page__section">
      <h2>Sample Water Quality Data</h2>
      <p>
        The following charts demonstrate typical water quality patterns observed
        in Central Texas streams during community monitoring efforts.
      </p>

      <div class="tst-page__chart-grid">
        <div class="tst-page__chart-card">
          <h3>Dissolved Oxygen vs Temperature</h3>
          <canvas id="doTemperatureChart"></canvas>
        </div>
        <div class="tst-page__chart-card">
          <h3>pH Stability Over Time</h3>
          <canvas id="phTimeChart"></canvas>
        </div>
        <div class="tst-page__chart-card tst-page__chart-card--wide">
          <h3>Turbidity Response to Precipitation</h3>
          <canvas id="turbidityChart"></canvas>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="tst-page__section tst-page__section--split">
      <div class="tst-page__prose">
        <h2>Environmental Anthropology and Sustainability Implications</h2>

        <h3>Community Science as Cultural Practice</h3>
        <p>
          Water quality monitoring through community science represents a
          contemporary form of environmental knowledge production that bridges
          scientific and local ways of understanding ecosystems. This practice
          embodies what anthropologist Anna Tsing calls "collaborative survival"
          — the ways humans and non-humans work together to maintain livable worlds.
        </p>
        <p>
          The standardization of monitoring protocols serves multiple functions
          beyond data collection. These practices create shared vocabularies and
          methods that enable diverse communities to participate in environmental
          governance.
        </p>

        <h3>Sustainability and Watershed Governance</h3>
        <p>
          Long-term water quality datasets generated through community monitoring
          create new possibilities for environmental management that extend beyond
          traditional technocratic approaches. By engaging local communities as
          data collectors and stewards, these programs build social capacity for
          adaptive management in the face of climate change and urban development
          pressures.
        </p>

        <h3>Methodological Contributions to Environmental Anthropology</h3>
        <p>
          Community-based monitoring programs offer environmental anthropologists
          unique opportunities to study the coproduction of scientific knowledge
          and environmental governance. The integration of quantitative water
          quality data with ethnographic observation creates opportunities for
          understanding how environmental change is experienced and interpreted by
          different communities.
        </p>
      </div>

      <aside class="tst-page__sidebar">
        <div class="tst-page__sidebar-card">
          <h4>Program Details</h4>
          <dl>
            <dt>Program</dt><dd>Texas Stream Team</dd>
            <dt>Scope</dt><dd>Statewide monitoring network</dd>
            <dt>Role</dt><dd>Community Scientist &amp; Anthropological Observer</dd>
            <dt>Focus</dt><dd>Water quality methods and environmental knowledge systems</dd>
            <dt>Duration</dt><dd>Ongoing monitoring since 2019</dd>
          </dl>
        </div>

        <div class="tst-page__sidebar-card">
          <h4>Key Methods</h4>
          <ul>
            <li>Standardized water quality protocols</li>
            <li>Community science training</li>
            <li>Participatory data validation</li>
            <li>Ethnographic observation</li>
            <li>Environmental education</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .tst-page {
    max-width: var(--shell-max);
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: var(--space-9) var(--gutter) var(--space-10);
  }

  .tst-page__header {
    max-width: var(--measure-wide);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-10);
  }

  .tst-page__breadcrumb {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: var(--step--1);
    letter-spacing: var(--tracking-wider);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--ink-faint);
    font-weight: 500;
    display: flex;
    gap: var(--space-2);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-5);
  }

  .tst-page__breadcrumb a {
    color: var(--accent);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .tst-page__title {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: clamp(var(--step-4), 5vw, var(--step-6));
    font-weight: 400;
    letter-spacing: var(--tracking-tight);
    font-variation-settings: 'opsz' 144, 'SOFT' 30;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-5);
  }

  .tst-page__lede {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: var(--step-2);
    line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    max-width: var(--measure);
  }

  .tst-page__section {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-10);
  }

  .tst-page__section > h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: var(--step--1);
    letter-spacing: var(--tracking-wider);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--ink-faint);
    font-weight: 600;
    padding-bottom: var(--space-4);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-6);
  }

  .tst-page__section > p {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: var(--step-2);
    line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    max-width: var(--measure);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-6);
  }

  .tst-page__protocol-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(320px, 1fr));
    gap: var(--space-5);
  }

  .tst-page__protocol {
    padding: var(--space-6);
    border: 1px solid var(--rule);
  }

  .tst-page__protocol h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: var(--step-2);
    font-weight: 500;
    font-variation-settings: 'opsz' 144, 'SOFT' 40;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
    color: var(--accent);
  }

  .tst-page__protocol dl {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: auto 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-2) var(--space-4);
    font-size: var(--step-1);
  }

  .tst-page__protocol dt {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: var(--step--1);
    color: var(--ink-faint);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: var(--tracking-wider);
  }

  .tst-page__protocol dd {
    margin: 0;
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: var(--step--1);
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);
  }

  .tst-page__chart-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-6);
  }

  .tst-page__chart-card {
    padding: var(--space-5);
    border: 1px solid var(--rule);
  }

  .tst-page__chart-card h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: var(--step--1);
    letter-spacing: var(--tracking-wider);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--ink-faint);
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
  }

  .tst-page__chart-card--wide {
    grid-column: 1 / -1;
    max-width: 720px;
  }

  .tst-page__section--split {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 2fr 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-8);
    align-items: start;
  }

  .tst-page__prose h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: var(--step-3);
    font-weight: 500;
    font-variation-settings: 'opsz' 144, 'SOFT' 40;
    margin-top: var(--space-7);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
  }

  .tst-page__prose h3:first-child {
    margin-top: 0;
  }

  .tst-page__prose p {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: var(--step-2);
    line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-5);
    max-width: var(--measure);
  }

  .tst-page__sidebar {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-5);
    position: sticky;
    top: calc(var(--space-8) + 20px);
  }

  .tst-page__sidebar-card {
    padding: var(--space-5);
    border: 1px solid var(--rule);
    background: var(--paper-deep);
  }

  .tst-page__sidebar-card h4 {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: var(--step--1);
    letter-spacing: var(--tracking-wider);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--ink-faint);
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
  }

  .tst-page__sidebar-card dl {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: auto 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-2) var(--space-3);
    font-size: var(--step--1);
  }

  .tst-page__sidebar-card dt {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--ink);
  }

  .tst-page__sidebar-card dd {
    margin: 0;
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    color: var(--ink-soft);
  }

  .tst-page__sidebar-card ul {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: var(--step--1);
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-2);
  }

  .tst-page__sidebar-card li::before {
    content: '· ';
    color: var(--accent);
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  @media (max-width: 880px) {
    .tst-page__section--split {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
    .tst-page__sidebar {
      position: static;
    }
    .tst-page__chart-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>

<script is:inline src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/chart.js"></script>
<script is:inline>
  document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', function () {
    new Chart(document.getElementById('doTemperatureChart'), {
      type: 'line',
      data: {
        labels: ['15°C', '18°C', '21°C', '24°C', '27°C', '30°C', '33°C'],
        datasets: [{
          label: 'Dissolved Oxygen (mg/L)',
          data: [10.2, 9.1, 8.3, 7.6, 6.9, 6.1, 5.4],
          borderColor: 'rgba(54, 162, 235, 1)',
          backgroundColor: 'rgba(54, 162, 235, 0.2)',
          tension: 0.1
        }]
      },
      options: {
        responsive: true,
        plugins: { legend: { display: false } },
        scales: {
          y: { beginAtZero: false, title: { display: true, text: 'DO (mg/L)' } },
          x: { title: { display: true, text: 'Temperature' } }
        }
      }
    });

    new Chart(document.getElementById('phTimeChart'), {
      type: 'line',
      data: {
        labels: ['Jan','Feb','Mar','Apr','May','Jun','Jul','Aug','Sep','Oct','Nov','Dec'],
        datasets: [{
          label: 'pH',
          data: [7.8, 7.9, 7.7, 7.6, 7.4, 7.2, 7.1, 7.0, 7.2, 7.5, 7.7, 7.8],
          borderColor: 'rgba(75, 192, 192, 1)',
          backgroundColor: 'rgba(75, 192, 192, 0.2)',
          tension: 0.1
        }]
      },
      options: {
        responsive: true,
        plugins: { legend: { display: false } },
        scales: {
          y: { min: 6.5, max: 8.5, title: { display: true, text: 'pH (standard units)' } },
          x: { title: { display: true, text: 'Month' } }
        }
      }
    });

    new Chart(document.getElementById('turbidityChart'), {
      type: 'bar',
      data: {
        labels: ['Pre-rain', 'During storm', '1 day post', '3 days post', '7 days post', '14 days post'],
        datasets: [{
          label: 'Turbidity (NTU)',
          data: [5.2, 45.8, 28.3, 15.7, 8.9, 6.1],
          backgroundColor: 'rgba(255, 206, 86, 0.8)',
          borderColor: 'rgba(255, 206, 86, 1)',
          borderWidth: 1
        }]
      },
      options: {
        responsive: true,
        plugins: { legend: { display: false } },
        scales: {
          y: { beginAtZero: true, title: { display: true, text: 'Turbidity (NTU)' } },
          x: { title: { display: true, text: 'Time Relative to Precipitation Event' } }
        }
      }
    });
  });
</script>
